<p>I have the following code for a plugin for AppPresser which is supposed to show a loading icon over the page when the menu is clicked.</p>  <p>On an iPhone, the opaque black background shows but the loading icon (e.g. ajax-loading.png) which is a background image of a div on top of the opaque black background does not show. On Android it does show.</p>  <p>Here is the CSS:</p>  <pre><code>.apppresser-loading-screen-with-opaque-black-background {     opacity:0.5;     background:#000;     width:100%;     top:0;     left:0;     position:fixed;     z-index:100; }  .apppresser-loading-screen-with-image-background {     position:fixed;     z-index:1000;     left:0;     top:0;     width:100%;     background-repeat: no-repeat;     background-attachment: fixed;     background-position: center center;      background-color: transparent;     background-size:auto auto; } </code></pre>  <p>Here is the jQuery:     jQuery(document).ready(function ($) {</p>  <pre><code>    var menuTouched = false;     $('body').prepend('&lt;div class="apppresser-loading-screen-with-opaque-black-background"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;');     $('body').prepend('&lt;div class="apppresser-loading-screen-with-image-background"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;');     $('.apppresser-loading-screen-with-image-background').css('background-image', "url(" + apppresser_frontend_settings.src + ")");     $('.apppresser-loading-screen-with-image-background, .apppresser-loading-screen-with-opaque-black-background').css('height', $(window).height() + 'px');     $('.apppresser-loading-screen-with-opaque-black-background, .apppresser-loading-screen-with-image-background').hide(0);      $(window).bind('beforeunload', function () {         if (menuTouched) {             $("ul[class*='menu'], .secondary-toggle").hide(1000);             $('.apppresser-loading-screen-with-opaque-black-background,.apppresser-loading-screen-with-image-background').show(0);             $('.apppresser-loading-screen-with-image-background, .apppresser-loading-screen-with-opaque-black-background').css('display', 'block');         }     });      $(document).on('tap, touch, touchstart, click', "ul[class*='menu'] a", function () {         menuTouched = true;         return true;     });  }); </code></pre>  <p>apppresser_frontend_settings.src is added using wp_localize_script and is a url of an image that exists.</p>